<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-106-334 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 986 113</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  July 15 1991 v8 n28 p32(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Publisher uses ISDN ANI to cut costs, improve customer service.andO;(Simon andamp; Schuster, integrated services digital network, automaticnumber identification)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallace, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Book publisher Simon and Schuster has enhanced customer servicethrough the use of the automatic number identification (ANI)feature of Integrated Services Digital Network (ISDN) in order toquickly route incoming telephone calls to agents responsible forvarious sales regions.andP;  Simon and Schuster is among the first touse ANI to allow an automatic call distributor (ACD) to routecalls to the proper agent by mapping the area code of the incomingcall to an agent responsible for that area.andP;  The system shouldsave Simon and Schuster $55,000 per year in 800-number usagecharges and staff expenses.andP;  Customers reach the agents morequickly and spend less time on the phone.andP;  Special routing tableshad to be created in the Aspect Telecommunications ACD which wouldenable the switch to match the area code an incoming call's ANIwith the correct agent's extension.andP;  The company plans toeventually use ANI with a voice response unit-based system toautomate the stock checking, price verification and book orderingprocesses.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Simon and Schuster Inc. (Communication systems).andO;Topic:     ISDNAutomatic Call DistributorsAutomatic Number Identification (Telecommunications)Case Study.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>